        h3 3. How do we protect your information?
        div Our website is scanned on a regular basis for security holes and known vulnerabilities in order to make your visit to our site as safe as possible. your personal information is contained behind secured networks and is only accessible by a limited number of persons who have special access rights to such systems, and are required to keep the information confidential. In addition, all sensitive/credit information you supply is encrypted via Secure Socket Layer (SSL) technology. we implement a variety of security measures when a user enters, submits, or accesses their information to maintain the safety of your personal information. all transactions are processed through a gateway provider and are not stored or processed on our servers. we use Secure Connection that you can see it on the left of the web address of your browser, it has written Secure. But remember that no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

        h3 4. Do we use 'cookies'?
        div Yes. Cookies and similar technology are small files that a site or its service provider transfers to your computer's hard drive through your Web browser that enables the site's or service provider's systems to recognize your browser and capture and remember certain information. For instance, we use cookies or similar technology to help us remember and process the items in your shopping cart and sign up state. They are also used to help us understand your preferences based on previous or current site activity, which enables us to provide you with improved services. We also use cookies to help us compile aggregate data about site traffic and site interaction so that we can offer better site experiences and tools in the future. Cookies may be persistent or stored only during an individual session. we also may use web beacons to help us estimate the effectiveness of our content and other offerings.
        h4 We may use cookies to:
        ul.circle
            li Collection information and to improve our services.
            li Keep track of advertisements.
            li Tells us whether you have to allow us to use your geolocation data.
            li If you register on our site, we may use cookies to remember your registration information, so you do not need to log into our site each time you visit us. It is possible to choose to turn off (but not all) cookies. You do this through your browser settings or mobile device settings. Since the browser is a little different, look at your browser's Help Menu to learn the correct way to modify your cookies.

        b If users disable cookies in their browser:
        div If you turn cookies off it will turn off some of the services of the site.


        h3 5. Third Parties
